    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given the deterministic regulatory submission context and the absence of rate-dependent failure mechanisms at quasi-static loading speeds. The UQ campaign, including Sobol-index sensitivity analysis documented in Nagaraja-UQ-2024-v2, provides additional confidence that dominant uncertainty sources are well-characterised. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepts the FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated pedicle screw COU.",
